      <h1 id="title">Spray Tan</h1>
      <p>The result will last about a week but varies with each individual depending on their personal skin renewal cycle. The application takes about 10 to 15 minutes and drying time of 5 minutes.</p>
       
      <ul class="spray-tan">
      <strong>Before your spray tanning session:</strong>
          <li>EXFOLIATE and WAX all areas to be tanned before each session. Pay special attention to your knees, ankles, feet, elbows, and knuckles.</li>
          <li>Getting rid of dead skin before tanning will extend the life of the tan. If you donâ€™t exfoliate properly, the tan will start to flake off within 24 hours.</li>
          <li>No lotions, perfumes, body oils, make up, moisturizers, or sunscreens.</li>
          <li>Wear loose-fitting clothes, preferably dark colors.</li>
          <li>You may tan in the garment of your choice. Topless is fine as well as nude. Whatever you are comfortable with.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul class="spray-tan">
      <strong>After your spray tanning session:</strong>
          <li>Wait 6 to 8 hours before you shower. This will allow the solution to fully develop in the skin. The longer you wait to shower the better results.</li>
          <li>Moisturize the entire body, preferably twice a daily for at least one week.</li>
          <li>Avoid exfoliating the skin.</li>
          <li>Avoid long hot showers, hot tubs, and Jacuzzis. They speed up the exfoliation process.</li>
          <li>Avoid exercising immediately after your tanning session. Sweating will shorten life of your tan.</li>
          <li>Always apply sunscreen when exposed to the sun.</li>
      </ul>
    
